This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a generative model based on variational auto-encoders and generative adversarial neural networks. It also focuses on the disentangled latent space, which is a popular topic in machine learning research. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed model is applied to image datasets and aims to generate samples corresponding to various objects in a high variety of views. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a novel approach to multi-view data generation without view supervision, which is a problem that can be addressed using AI techniques. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks to build the generative model. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the problem of generating samples corresponding to different objects, which is a natural language processing task.
